  <name>Speak-to-AI</name>
  <summary>Offline speech-to-text for AI assistants</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      A minimalist, privacy-focused desktop application that enables voice input for AI assistants 
      without sending your voice to the cloud. Uses the Whisper model locally for speech recognition.
      Licensed under MIT License - free and open source software.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>100% offline speech recognition using Whisper.cpp</li>
      <li>System tray integration with recording status</li>
      <li>Configurable hotkeys including Microsoft Copilot key support</li>
      <li>Multiple output modes: clipboard, direct typing simulation</li>
      <li>Cross-platform support for X11 and Wayland</li>
      <li>Privacy-first: no data sent to external servers</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
